  "designNotes": [
    "Simplest LiPo charger option -- only needs a programming resistor and input cap",
    "Use 10k PROG resistor for 100mA charge rate (safe for 300mAh+ batteries)",
    "STAT pin can drive an LED through a 1k resistor to indicate charging status",
    "Place 4.7uF ceramic caps on both VDD (input) and VBAT (output)",
    "No reverse polarity protection -- add a Schottky diode on VBUS if needed",
    "Thermal regulation limits charge current if IC gets too hot -- good for small PCBs",
    "Suitable for keyboards when MCU does not have built-in charger (e.g., Holyiot 18010)"
  ],
  "concerns": [
    "No power path management — system loses power during USB disconnect",
    "Maximum 500mA charge current — slow for batteries >1000mAh",
    "No reverse polarity protection — add external Schottky diode",
    "No battery detection — will try to charge even without battery",
    "Single-cell only — cannot charge multi-cell packs"
